The Plateau State Police Command has arrested one Moses Oko, suspected to be the killer of one Miss Jennifer Anthony, a 300-level student of the University of Jos. It was gathered that Anthony was said to have been missing since December 30, 2021, but her lifeless and mutilated body was found on 1st January 2022 at a hotel in Jos, the state capital. It was further learned that the deceased was a student of Special Education and Rehabilitation Sciences. FG Strengthens Health Regulatory Agencies To Actualise Mandate –… 2023: Orji Uzor Kalu Wants Presidency Zoned To South-East However, the Commissioner of Police in the State, Bartholomew Onyeka said, “Following the gruesome murder of Miss Jennifer Anthony, a 300-level student of the University of Jos whose lifeless body was found mutilated on 1st January 2022 at Domus Pacis Guest House, Jos, by a man named Moses Oko aged 20 years.” “He is suspected to be her boyfriend who fled after committing the crime.” “The Command in a bid to arrest the perpetrator launched an aggressive manhunt on the suspect and tactically trailed him to Benue State where he was arrested by hawk-eyed police operatives of the Command,’’ he added.